Key Match Events: Abdoulaye Seck headed home a Krepin Diatta free-kick to give the Lions of Teranga a deserved lead shortly past the hour mark
Iliman Ndiaye wrapped up the victory on the cusp of stoppage time with a tidy assist from Sadio Mane
Post-Match Reflections: Guinea finish third, but four points will be enough to take one of those four slots for the best third-place group finishers
Cameroon will now face Group A runners-up Nigeria at the Felix Houphouet Boigny Stadium in Abidjan on Saturday night for a place in the quarter-finals
Guinea look set to face surprise Group A winners Equatorial Guinea at Abidjan's Alassane Ouattara Stadium on Sunday
Senegal will meet a third-place team from Group A or F - so either hosts Ivory Coast or likely one of DR Congo, Zambia or Tanzania - back at the Charles Konan Banny Stadium next Monday night
Miscellaneous Highlights: Sadio Mane missed a huge chance and also saw a goal chalked off for offside
That third Gambia goal in Bouake was eventually ruled out for handball
Cameroon went 3-2 ahead and were going through in second place at Guinea's expense for a moment, but it's now 3-3!
Chelsea's Nicolas Jackson has just replaced Habib Diallo for Senegal
Fulham's Fode Ballo-Toure is also on
